# Itervox coding rules (Cursor)

This rule activates for every Cursor session on the itervox repository. The full rule set lives in two places that you MUST read before making changes:

1. `CLAUDE.md` at the repo root — architecture invariants, package dependency order, `cfgMu` guard list, frontend architecture, hard rules.
2. `AGENTS.md` at the repo root — index of focused rule bundles and verification commands.

The detailed bundles live under `.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`. The directory name is historical; the content is tool-agnostic plain markdown and applies to Cursor the same way it applies to every other coding agent.

## Read the right bundle before editing

| When you are editing… | Read this file first |
|---|---|
| `internal/orchestrator/**/*.go`, adding concurrent code, mutable `cfg.*` fields | `.claude/skills/orchestrator-invariants/SKILL.md` |
| `web/src/**/*.{ts,tsx}` that makes HTTP or SSE calls (outside `web/src/auth/`) | `.claude/skills/authed-transport/SKILL.md` |
| `web/src/components/**` / `web/src/pages/**` — React component work | `.claude/skills/react-component-discipline/SKILL.md` |
| New Go file, file past ~400 lines, new helper, new package | `.claude/skills/go-package-hygiene/SKILL.md` |
| `internal/config/config.go` struct fields, `WORKFLOW.md` schema evolution | `.claude/skills/config-field-checklist/SKILL.md` |
| Before editing exported symbols / HTTP routes / SSE events / Zod schemas | `.claude/skills/change-impact-review/SKILL.md` |
| When the impact review surfaces a BREAKING change (hard stop) | `.claude/skills/breaking-change-gate/SKILL.md` |
| `go.mod`, `Makefile`, Go toolchain bumps, govulncheck stdlib findings | `.claude/skills/go-toolchain-sync/SKILL.md` |
| Before claiming complete, before committing, before opening a PR | `.claude/skills/verify-before-done/SKILL.md` |

## Commands

- `/interview` (`.claude/commands/interview.md`) — 8-question structured interview for new features
- `/brainstorm` (`.claude/commands/brainstorm.md`) — 3-subagent design debate with tradeoffs table

## Non-negotiable rules

- **Single-goroutine state machine**: never mutate `orchestrator.State` from a worker goroutine. Use the `o.events` channel. See `orchestrator-invariants`.
- **Bearer-auth transport**: never call raw `fetch()` or `new EventSource()` in `web/src/` outside `web/src/auth/`. Use `authedFetch` and `openAuthedEventStream`. See `authed-transport`.
- **Toolchain lockstep**: `go.mod`'s `go` directive and `Makefile`'s `GOTOOLCHAIN` must match byte-for-byte. Bump both together. See `go-toolchain-sync`.
- **Race detector mandatory**: `go test -race ./...` must pass. The race detector is non-deterministic — stress with `-count=5` on new concurrent code.
- **Verification gate**: `make verify` must exit 0 before claiming done. `go test ./...` alone is insufficient — it misses lint, coverage, and frontend regressions. See `verify-before-done`.
- **Never commit `.env`**: secrets live in `.itervox/.env` (gitignored) or environment variables.

## Quick commands

```bash
make verify                              # full local CI equivalent
go test -race ./...                      # Go test with race detector
cd web && pnpm test:coverage             # frontend tests + 70% coverage gate
govulncheck -tags dev ./...              # after bumping Go deps
```

Every claim of "tests pass" or "ready to merge" must be accompanied by evidence — show the exit code of the command you ran.
